  "text": "## gRPC Error Status Propagation Across Go Services\n\nThis analysis examines how gRPC error status codes are created and propagated to HTTP responses across three major Go projects: kubernetes/kubernetes, grafana/grafana, and etcd-io/etcd.\n\n### Kubernetes/kubernetes\n\n**Error Creation:**\n- `pkg/kubelet/apis/grpc/ratelimit.go`: Defines `ErrorLimitExceeded` as a package-level gRPC error with `codes.ResourceExhausted` (line 31)\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/kubelet/pkg/cri/streaming/errors.go`: The `NewErrorTooManyInFlight()` function creates errors with `codes.ResourceExhausted` (line 28-30)\n- Various service files (CSI mock services, KMS plugins) create domain-specific errors using `status.Error()` with specific codes like `codes.NotFound`, `codes.Internal`, `codes.InvalidArgument`\n\n**Error Propagation to HTTP:**\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/kubelet/pkg/cri/streaming/errors.go`: The `WriteError()` function (lines 32-51) is the central translation point. It:\n  - Extracts the gRPC status code using `grpcstatus.FromError()`\n  - Maps codes to HTTP status codes via a switch statement:\n    - `codes.NotFound` → `http.StatusNotFound`\n    - `codes.ResourceExhausted` → `http.StatusTooManyRequests` (with Retry-After header)\n    - All others → `http.StatusInternalServerError`\n  - Writes the HTTP response with appropriate headers\n\n- `pkg/kubelet/server/server.go`: Calls `streaming.WriteError()` to convert gRPC errors to HTTP responses when handling streaming requests (lines 958-1046)\n\n### Grafana/grafana\n\n**Error Creation:**\n- `pkg/services/grpcserver/interceptors/auth.go`: Creates authentication-related errors with:\n  - `codes.Unauthenticated` for invalid tokens and missing authorization (lines 71, 79, 104, 114, 118, 124, 144, 150, 154)\n  - `codes.PermissionDenied` for permission violations (line 118)\n- `pkg/services/authz/rbac/service.go`: Returns `codes.NotFound` errors for unsupported resources (lines 1023, 597, 862)\n- `pkg/services/authz/zanzana/server/auth.go`: Creates `codes.Unauthenticated` errors for various auth failures\n- Generated gRPC service stubs (e.g., in `pkg/services/authz/proto/v1/extention_grpc.pb.go`) return `codes.Unimplemented` for unimplemented methods\n\n**Error Propagation to HTTP:**\n- `pkg/storage/unified/resource/errors.go`: The `AsErrorResult()` function (lines 121-165) converts errors to HTTP responses by:\n  - Checking for Kubernetes API errors first using `errors.As()`\n  - Extracting gRPC status using `grpcstatus.FromError()`\n  - Converting gRPC codes to HTTP status codes using `runtime.HTTPStatusFromCode()` from grpc-gateway (line 158)\n  - Wrapping in `resourcepb.ErrorResult` with HTTP status code\n\n- `pkg/services/authz/zanzana/server/openfga_server.go`: Sets up gRPC-gateway handlers with custom error handlers (lines 223-234):\n  - Uses `runtime.WithErrorHandler()` to customize HTTP error responses\n  - Converts gRPC status to encoded error codes\n  - Applies custom HTTP middleware for error formatting\n\n### etcd-io/etcd\n\n**Error Creation:**\n- `api/v3rpc/rpctypes/error.go`: Defines a comprehensive set of package-level gRPC status errors (lines 23-98) with specific codes:\n  - `ErrGRPCEmptyKey`, `ErrGRPCKeyNotFound`: `codes.InvalidArgument`\n  - `ErrGRPCCompacted`, `ErrGRPCFutureRev`: `codes.OutOfRange`\n  - `ErrGRPCNoSpace`: `codes.ResourceExhausted`\n  - `ErrGRPCMemberNotFound`: `codes.NotFound`\n  - `ErrGRPCNoLeader`, `ErrGRPCTimeout`: `codes.Unavailable`\n  - `ErrGRPCPermissionDenied`: `codes.PermissionDenied`\n  - Many others with `codes.FailedPrecondition`\n\n**Error Translation:**\n- `server/etcdserver/api/v3rpc/util.go`: The `togRPCError()` function (lines 98-108) maps internal server errors to pre-defined gRPC status errors:\n  - Maintains a `toGRPCErrorMap` (lines 35-96) that maps internal error types to gRPC status errors\n  - For unmapped errors, returns `status.Error(codes.Unknown, err.Error())`\n  - Preserves context-based errors (Canceled, DeadlineExceeded) for special handling\n\n**Error Propagation to HTTP:**\n- `api/etcdserverpb/gw/rpc.pb.gw.go`, `server/etcdserver/api/v3election/v3electionpb/gw/v3election.pb.gw.go`, `server/etcdserver/api/v3lock/v3lockpb/gw/v3lock.pb.gw.go`: Generated gRPC-gateway code that:\n  - Automatically translates gRPC errors to HTTP responses\n  - Uses marshaler to decode requests (lines 660-661, etc.)\n  - Returns `status.Errorf(codes.InvalidArgument, ...)` for malformed requests\n  - The gRPC-gateway runtime handles conversion of gRPC codes to HTTP status codes\n\n- `server/embed/serve.go`: Registers the gateway with custom error handlers for HTTP-to-gRPC conversion (lines 322-324)\n\n### Key Differences in Approaches\n\n1. **Error Definition:**\n   - **Kubernetes**: Defines errors inline in utility functions\n   - **Grafana**: Creates errors in interceptors and service methods\n   - **etcd**: Pre-defines all errors as package-level variables for reuse\n\n2. **Error Translation Strategy:**\n   - **Kubernetes**: Manual switch-case mapping in `WriteError()`\n   - **Grafana**: Uses grpc-gateway's built-in `runtime.HTTPStatusFromCode()` utility\n   - **etcd**: Maps internal errors to pre-defined gRPC errors, then relies on grpc-gateway for HTTP conversion\n\n3. **HTTP Status Code Mapping:**\n   - **Kubernetes**: Explicit mapping in the `WriteError()` function\n   - **Grafana**: Leverages grpc-gateway's standard gRPC-to-HTTP code mapping\n   - **etcd**: Relies entirely on grpc-gateway's automatic conversion based on gRPC status codes\n\n4. **Gateway Integration:**\n   - **Kubernetes**: No gRPC-gateway; direct HTTP-to-gRPC conversion in streaming server\n   - **Grafana**: Uses grpc-gateway v2 with custom error handlers and middleware\n   - **etcd**: Uses grpc-gateway for REST API translation with generated handlers\n\nThe common pattern across all three is the use of Google's gRPC status package to define errors with specific codes, which then get translated to HTTP status codes either manually or through gRPC-gateway's runtime utilities."
}

